                    <article class="box7">
                        <h3>Market Exposure</h3>
                        <p>
                            One of the basic principles of <strong>alt.bet</strong> is that a customer is only allowed to risk funds
                            that are available in their account.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Market exposure is the term that represents the amount of money that has been reserved to cover the
                            unmatched and matched orders placed on your account.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Each time you place an order (a bet), or make a change to an unmatched order, your market exposure will
                            be adjusted accordingly.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <strong>alt.bet</strong> will also reserve funds to cover the trading fees you will have to pay once your
                            order has been
                            settled.
                        </p>
                    </article>

